abstract: More than 30 around the world have acted in the face of recession fears. Economists warn of a currency-tied competition.
snippet: More than 30 around the world have acted in the face of recession fears. Economists warn of a currency-tied competition.
lead_paragraph: More than 30 central banks around the world have cut interest rates this year, as countries move to shore up their economies amid rising concerns over global growth, trade conflicts and the threat of a messy Brexit.

abstract: Invoking the poem at her base is the wrong response to Trump’s latest move to keep out nonwhite immigrants.
snippet: Invoking the poem at her base is the wrong response to Trump’s latest move to keep out nonwhite immigrants.
lead_paragraph: I’m really glad we’re having a discussion about what the Statue of Liberty means to America, even if it is precipitated by nefarious thinking. This week, the Trump administration moved forward with a change in legal immigration policy that will limit people allowed to enter the country to those who are well enough off not to need public assistance. It is called the “public charge” rule.

abstract: “Give me your tired and your poor who can stand on their own two feet,” said Kenneth T. Cuccinelli II, a top Trump administration immigration official. His remarks set off a controversy.
snippet: “Give me your tired and your poor who can stand on their own two feet,” said Kenneth T. Cuccinelli II, a top Trump administration immigration official. His remarks set off a controversy.
lead_paragraph: Kenneth T. Cuccinelli II, one of the Trump administration’s top immigration officials, set off a controversy this week with comments about “The New Colossus,” the 136-year-old sonnet at the base of the Statue of Liberty.

headline_main: ‘Huddled Masses’ in Statue of Liberty Poem Are European, Trump Official Says

abstract: Critics and allies said President Trump’s relative disinterest in human rights and focus on economics have kept him from taking sides between China and the protesters.
snippet: Critics and allies said President Trump’s relative disinterest in human rights and focus on economics have kept him from taking sides between China and the protesters.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, presenting himself as a neutral observer of the mass protests in Hong Kong, offered lukewarm support on Tuesday for pro-democracy demonstrators there but stopped short of criticizing the government in Beijing.

abstract: Mr. Trump railed against China, President Obama, the lawsuits he’s facing, and, as always, his media coverage.

lead_paragraph: MONACA, Pa. — President Trump’s appearance on Tuesday at the site of a multibillion-dollar chemical plant under construction here was ostensibly about energy policy.

abstract: Revisiting the blistering criticism from President Trump’s own party raises questions about whether the search for a killer line on Mr. Trump is a fool’s errand for Democrats in 2020.
snippet: Revisiting the blistering criticism from President Trump’s own party raises questions about whether the search for a killer line on Mr. Trump is a fool’s errand for Democrats in 2020.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has called President Trump an “existential threat” to the nation.

headline_main: Stacey Abrams Will Not Run for President in 2020, Focusing Instead on Fighting Voter Suppression
headline_print_headline: Abrams Shifts Her Focus To Bolstering Voter Rights

abstract: The New Jersey senator and a few other Democratic candidates are detouring from early-voting states to spend time in Detroit, Philadelphia and Milwaukee.
snippet: The New Jersey senator and a few other Democratic candidates are detouring from early-voting states to spend time in Detroit, Philadelphia and Milwaukee.
lead_paragraph: MILWAUKEE — An energized crowd of 500 packed into a mixed-use space here on a summer Sunday afternoon to hear a rousing stump speech from Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey, who was making the final stop in a 12-day campaign blitz in a state that won’t hold its primary until April.
